# Character_Sheets

## 1. Applies when
Important characters, companions / NPCs / faction figures, arc-driven plot, or
personal requests and relationship events.

## 2. This document owns
Identity; psychological arc; key props; dialogue style; narrative function;
relationships; personal-interaction index.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Gameplay numbers; skill multipliers; full mission flow; economy rules.

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. Per-character sheets · 3. Arcs · 4. Key props ·
5. Relationships · 6. Personal-interaction index · 7. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- Character vs Gameplay — narrative meaning of a mechanic vs its numbers.
- Character vs Naming — usage vs the naming system.
- Personal-interaction index points to Mission (request flow lives there).

## 6. Common audit rules
- No concrete gameplay numbers here (enforced by a `CHAR-NO-…-STATS` boundary check).
- Numbers link back to Gameplay_Systems; requests link to Mission_Design.
